br.com.caelum.vraptor.interceptor.multipart

Class Servlet3MultipartInterceptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • br.com.caelum.vraptor.interceptor.multipart.Servlet3MultipartInterceptor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Interceptor, MultipartInterceptor

    @Intercepts(before=ParametersInstantiatorInterceptor.class)
@RequestScoped
public class Servlet3MultipartInterceptor
extends java.lang.Object
implements MultipartInterceptor

    A multipart interceptor based on Servlet3 File Upload. It's only enabled if Servlet Part is avaliable. If you're using servlet3 upload features, the MultipartConfig.getDirectory() has no effect.

    TODO This interceptor fails in Apache Tomcat 7.x because request.getParts() doesn't work in a Filter. So you need to use CommonsUploadMultipartInterceptor. See bug https://issues.apache.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=49711 and https://servlet-spec-public.dev.java.net/issues/show_bug.cgi?id=14 for more info.

    TODO According JSR315, all form fields are also avaliable via request.getParameter and request.getParameters(), but not all containers implements this issue (Glassfish 3.0 fails).

    Since:
    3.2
